	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Beastlord is a monk/shaman hybrid.&nbsp;&nbsp;He/she will have most low to mid-level shaman spells, including a pet, and have weight/weapon limits of a monk.  The Beastlord will potentially be a worthy soloer, as most hybrids *can* be, considering considerable offensive prowess, combined with some reasonable buffs/healing/dd/dot.  They may end up being too similar to Rangers/Paladins, though.  These three hybrids are all based on a fighter class, and a healer class.  The Shadowknight is great because it's a mix between a fighter, and a true caster.  One of a kind.  I would have liked to see an enchanting rogue...  Techniques/personalities somewhat are similar already.  Brain-stabbers?  No?  Okay...  Well, anyway...  It'll be fun to figure out how to roleplay it, at least.  Esoteric chanting, and strange, sometimes downright nasty spellmaking techniques, combined with extremely disciplined, and spiritual fighters.  Hmm...   Anyway, good luck.  Be safe, all.<br>&nbsp;<br>Hyden Endabrush<br>Expert Scout of the Fay</td></tr>
